For additional comparison, after around 170 tests, Sachin had an average of 57, while Smith, after 112 tests, is currently at 56. Additionally, Tendulkar had an average of 60 after a similar number of tests. So even if we set aside the DRS factor or the influences of different eras, it is evident that Sachin stands far ahead of Smith in Tests regardless.

